lead_paragraph: The deaths of nine people who were killed on Anchorage trails, parks or isolated streets since January remain unsolved — among them three cases involving two victims each.

headline.print_headline: Anchorage Is Alarmed by Unsolved Killings
headline.main: Unsolved Homicides in Anchorage Alarm Residents and Baffle Police

snippet: The deaths of nine people who were killed on Anchorage trails, parks or isolated streets since January remain unsolved — among them three cases involving two victims each....
abstract: Residents and authorities in Anchorage are on edge following series of nine unsolved homicides, dating back to January 2016, in which victims were killed outdoors on isolated trails or streets; anxiety has been exacerbated by fact that city has recorded 25 homicides so far in 2016, exceeding total for entire previous year.
